  "label": "Courtyardlight Bedchamber",
  "description": "Courtyardlight Bedchamber constitutes a compact sleeping room opening onto the house’s inward court, where ribbed saltglass panes impose a steady, pale illumination. Basalt walls carry a mineral-wash finish and shallow buttress ribs that register the residence’s engineering against Brineshade’s tidal stresses. A low sleeping dais and built-in niches are cut directly into the masonry, minimizing loose furnishings in the mineral-laden air. Light is further regulated by a shuttered interior screen and layered baffles that reduce terminator glare without extinguishing optical clarity.",
